Please answer my code questions using the given API following this format: <<<api>>>: $API
<<<code>>>: $CODE
<<<explanation>>>: $EXPLANATION.
For API Iterator.next, the API usage rule is: Get the next element from an Iterator if it has more elements.

Question: How to replace a element in list of objects from another list: :I have a List of ImagesList<Image> images = getImages();Image.javapublic class Image {    private String imageId;    // getter and setter methods    // ...}And I have a List<String> imageIds to replace the imageId in each Image object. What would be the best way to do it?
Please using this api: Iterator.next.
Answer:
response:
<<<api>>>: Iterator.next
<<<code>>>: 
List<Image> images = getImages();
List<String> imageIds = getImageIds();

Iterator<Image> iterator = images.iterator();
for (String imageId : imageIds) {
    if (iterator.hasNext()) {
        Image image = iterator.next();
        image.setImageId(imageId);
    } else {
        break;
    }
}

<<<explanation>>>: 
To replace the imageId in each Image object with the values from the imageIds list, you can use an iterator to iterate over the images list. For each imageId in the imageIds list, you can check if the iterator has a next element using the hasNext() method. If it does, you can retrieve the next image object using the next() method and set its imageId using the setImageId() method. If the iterator does not have a next element, you can break out of the loop. This ensures that only the number of imageIds available in the imageIds list are replaced in the images list.
